	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />For uncompressed text, the process is basically that, just with newer tools. I don't do a lot of hacking, so maybe there's some good tool to locate uncompressed text in ROMs I'm not aware of.
<br />
<br />Compressed text will always be much more difficult, because each game uses its own compression scheme, that has to be individually reverse engineered (unless someone else has already done it and provided documents/tools).

		

